---
import SupportPage from '../components/SupportPage.astro';
---
<SupportPage
  locale="en"
  path="/support.html"
  title="Support | GYUTRON Industrial Hardware"
  description="Technical and commercial support for GYUTRON machine vision, sensing, scanning, measurement and rugged computing hardware. Contact channels, response times and what to include in a request."
  eyebrow="Help & Support"
  heading="Support"
  crumb="Support"
  intro="Engineering-led support for GYUTRON industrial hardware — from product selection and integration to warranty and after-sales service for global B2B teams."
>
  <p class="support-lead">Whether you are evaluating a sensor, integrating a camera into a production line, or servicing a deployed fleet, our application and support engineers are here to help.</p>

  <h2>Contact channels</h2>
  <div class="support-channels">
    <div class="support-channel">
      <i class="fa-solid fa-envelope"></i>
      <h3>Email</h3>
      <p>General &amp; technical support, documentation and RMA requests.</p>
      <a href="mailto:info@gyutron.com">info@gyutron.com</a>
    </div>
    <div class="support-channel">
      <i class="fa-brands fa-whatsapp"></i>
      <h3>WhatsApp</h3>
      <p>Quick pre-sales and integration questions during business hours.</p>
      <a href="https://wa.me/85269509801">+852 6950 9801</a>
    </div>
    <div class="support-channel">
      <i class="fa-solid fa-headset"></i>
      <h3>Sales engineering</h3>
      <p>Specifications, quotations, samples and project scoping.</p>
      <a href="/contact-sales.html">Contact Sales →</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>What to include in a support request</h2>
  <p>To help us resolve your case quickly, please provide:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Product model and serial number</strong> (e.g. GY-A90 Touch, GY-CR720) plus firmware / software version where applicable.</li>
    <li><strong>A description of the application</strong> — host platform, interface (GigE Vision / USB3 / IO-Link / RS-232/485 / digital I/O) and operating environment.</li>
    <li><strong>What you expected versus what happened</strong>, with photos, sample images, logs or error codes where available.</li>
    <li><strong>Quantity and timeline</strong> for commercial or RMA requests.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Response times</h2>
  <p>Support is handled by our teams in Hong Kong and Shenzhen during standard business hours (GMT+8), Monday to Friday. We aim to acknowledge new requests within one business day. Complex integration or RMA cases may require additional review with our engineering team.</p>

  <h2>Self-service</h2>
  <p>Many questions are answered in our <a href="/support/faq.html">Frequently Asked Questions</a>. See also <a href="/support/warranty.html">Warranty</a> and <a href="/support/shipping-delivery.html">Shipping &amp; Delivery</a>.</p>

  <h2>Offices</h2>
  <p><strong>Hong Kong Headquarters</strong> — Hong Kong Science Park, Shatin, New Territories, Hong Kong SAR<br />
  <strong>Shenzhen R&amp;D Center</strong> — Shenzhen Bay Technology and Ecology Park, Nanshan District, Shenzhen, Guangdong, China</p>
</SupportPage>
